JOHANNESBURG – The fate of President Jacob Zuma is being discussed at the ANC's National Executive Committee meeting in Pretoria. Sources said the issue was raised from the floor.The NEC is believed to have assigned officials to negotiate an exit plan for Zuma. READ: ANC NEC meets to set lekgotla agenda ANC Secretary General Ace Magashule had said Zuma’s fate was not on the agenda of the meeting when addressing the media at the Saint George Hotel in Irene, Pretoria on Thursday. The party's president Cyril Ramaphosa is said to have told the meeting earlier he was working well with Zuma and that he was managing the transition. Ramaphosa met with Zuma earlier this month, but details of that meeting were never revealed. eNCA